cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS

The paper proposes a reinforcement learning algorithm that combines active learning and multi-step TD algorithm. It focuses on learning off-policy without the need for importance sampling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with learning algorithms. The paper also involves decision making and control tasks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The algorithm is evaluated on both discrete and continuous space tasks, which suggests it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of a binary classifier, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
